OL,5,CStarmer
OL,7,FAt a meeting with some of the families
OL,8,Fof those killed at Hillsborough, Sir
OL,9,FKeir acknowledged it had been a
OL,10,Fbattle, with "frank" discussions
OL,11,Fcontinuing as his deadline passed.
OL,13,FMargaret Aspinall, whose son James,
OL,14,F18, died at Hillsborough, said she is
OL,15,Fhopeful the new law "will mean no one
OL,16,Fwill ever have to suffer like we did".
OL,18,FSpeaking alongside Sir Keir in No 10,
OL,19,Fshe said: "I thought this is a day
OL,20,Fthat was not going to happen."
OL,26,@rD@NOUrD@TO]wD@UOUxD@eO]{D@KOU|D@^O]
